<!--
  HC career-performance commodity. Drives the per-shift Performance bar in
  the expanded Career Panel (PerformanceDetails.as in the Olympus UI) and
  the promotion/demotion/firing thresholds in EA's CareerLevel logic.

  CLASS: Commodity, NOT bare Statistic
  ------------------------------------
  EA's `CareerLevel.performance_stat` field is documented (in
  `simulation.zip:careers/career_tuning.pyc:CareerLevel.INSTANCE_TUNABLES`) as:

      'performance_stat': sims4.tuning.tunable.TunableReference(
          services.get_instance_manager(sims4.resources.Types.STATISTIC),
          description="Commodity used to track career performance for this level.",
          export_modes=ExportModes.All,
          tuning_group=GroupNames.SCORING),

  The TunableReference's manager is STATISTIC (which holds both Statistic
  and Commodity classes since Commodity extends Statistic — see
  `statistics/commodity.pyc:class Commodity(TunedContinuousStatistic, ..., manager=STATISTIC)`),
  but the description says "Commodity".  The CareerLevel runtime references
  the commodity-specific interface — convergence, distress thresholds,
  off-lot simulation flags, `_add_if_not_in_tracker` etc.  A bare Statistic
  is accepted at the TunableReference layer but Sims 4 1.124.55 silently
  REJECTS THE WHOLE RESOURCE when it doesn't pass the Commodity validation
  expected by the consumer.  Verified empirically: 0..5 Statistic registered
  fine (1157 STATISTIC manager count) but -100..+100 Statistic dropped it
  (1156 count) — because the negative-min only makes sense as a Commodity.

  RANGE -100..+100
  ----------------
  Matches every adult-career performance commodity EA ships (Writer,
  Entertainer, Criminal, Culinary, …).  Critical for our existing
  Career-level scoring tunables, which the previous 0..5 range silently
  disabled:

      promote_performance_level=100.0   (EA default; reached at max perf)
      demotion_performance_level=-80.0  (EA default; demoted if you sink)
      fired_performance_level=-95.0     (EA default; fired if you tank)
      career_performance_warning.threshold.value=-50  (HC tuning;
                                                       warn at half-tank)
      performance_metrics.base_performance=8           (per shift)
      performance_per_completed_goal=5                 (per completed task)
      missed_work_penalty=35                           (skipping work)

  At 0..5 a single completed task saturated the bar; at -100..+100 each
  shift moves the bar ~10-20 points, completing a daily-task line takes
  ~2 weeks, promotion is realistic, and the demotion/firing thresholds
  finally fire.

  WHY NOT EMIT A SimData COMPANION
  --------------------------------
  Tried in commit aabcb30 (schema hash 0x8273c673, 3 cols max/min/stat_name).
  Sims 4 also dropped the tuning when the SimData was present, even with
  byte-identical layout to EA's reference.  Backed out in 057541c.  The C++
  runtime SHOULD read `PerformanceStaticData.min_value`/`.max_value` from
  the Commodity's SimData on the AS3 side — without it, the Career Panel
  ProgressBar throws "Maximum cannot be equal to minimum" on expand.  That's
  a deferred problem (open in lastUIException analysis); fixing the silent
  career-add regression takes priority.

  COMMODITY TUNABLES PROVIDED
  ---------------------------
  Per `statistics/commodity.pyc:Commodity.INSTANCE_TUNABLES`:
    min_value_tuning              int    -100        min stat value
    max_value_tuning              int    +100        max stat value
    initial_tuning                tuple  (0, init=True)  starts at neutral
    visible                       bool   False       not in motive panel
                                                     (career panel reads it
                                                     via different path)
    remove_on_convergence         bool   False       persist while in career
    _add_if_not_in_tracker        bool   True        auto-add when used
    initial_as_default            bool   True        test default = 0
    instance_if_not_default       bool   True        always instantiate
                                                     (we don't decay so the
                                                     "save space" optimization
                                                     doesn't apply)
-->
<I c="Commodity" i="commodity" m="statistics.commodity" n="HC_Statistic_HistorianLevel" s="TBD_INSTANCE_ID">
  <T n="min_value_tuning">-100</T>
  <T n="max_value_tuning">100</T>
  <U n="initial_tuning">
    <T n="_initial_value">0</T>
    <T n="_use_stat_value_on_init">True</T>
  </U>
  <T n="visible">False</T>
  <T n="remove_on_convergence">False</T>
  <T n="_add_if_not_in_tracker">True</T>
  <T n="initial_as_default">True</T>
  <T n="instance_if_not_default">True</T>
</I>
